-- NUM Union Says 2 Miners Die at Gold Fields and Simmer Mines in Accidents
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-11-17T08:34:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/num-union-says-2-miners-die-at-gold-fields-and-simmer-mines-in-accidents.html
Two mineworkers died in accidents at
operations owned by Gold Fields Ltd. and Simmer and Jack Mines
Ltd., the National Union of Mineworkers said in an e-mailed
statement today.  A worker died in a locomotive accident at Simmer’s
Buffelsfontein mine in South Africa and a worker at Gold Fields’
Driefontein mine died in a rockfall, the union said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  